    <條號>Article 36</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The standards for hearing acuity examinations are as follows:
The unaided hearing acuity of each (right and left) ear, shall demonstrate the ability to hear the 40 dB or less of a signal at the frequency of 500, 1000 or 2000 hertz (cycles per second) and to hear the 50 dB or less of a signal at the frequency of 3000 hertz (cycles per second).
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 37</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[In respect of the examination for mouth, none of the followings which affect the airmen’s ability to safely perform duties shall be found:
1. Speech difficulty, un-clear speech or having stuttering
2. Deformity or other pathological conditions
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 38</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Airmen shall not have any communicable diseases which are statutorily classified by the Act of Prevention and Control of Communicable Diseases (of the Republic of China).
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <編章節>   Chapter Four- Waiver on Medical Exam</編章節>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 39</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[An airman who failed to pass the Medical Exam, in addition to seek for the remedy provided under Article 8 hereof, may submit to CAA an application with relevant documents within 30 days for the Waiver on Medical Exam from the date on which the notification of the determination of the failure is received. After CAA evaluation, recognizes through the working experience or cured by medical therapy，will not affect the safety of the flight, such fail items may be waived.
While The applicant request the Waiver on Medical Exam，the reconsideration of determination period should be suspended. Upon the reason for suspension of such period of time specified in the preceding paragraph ceases to exist, the period of time shall resume accruing taking into account of the time having accrued before such suspension.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 40</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[An applicant who failed pass on physical check  and his illness（or defect） is being developing and not in a stable condition, or one of the following illness（or defect） is found in his medical history, such airman shall not be eligible to apply for the Waiver on Medical Exam:
· Personality or behaviors disorders or psychological disturbances
· Chronic alcoholism or drug addiction
· Epilepsy
· Having had loss of consciousness in the medical history without identified cause
· Having had heart transplant surgery
· Wearing cardiac pacemaker
· Diabetes requiring medication for control
· Cerebral vascular diseases
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 41</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The Waiver on Medical Exam may be granted by any of the followings:
1. It may be granted by the results of assessments made by the medical institutes or specialized aviation medical doctors.
2. It may be granted by perform the actual duty, assessed by CAA authorized personnel.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 42</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[when CAA grants the Waiver on Medical Exams, the following item waived shall noted on medical certificate:
1. Expiration period of the waiver items
2. The condition of healthcare of the aviation medicine
3. The limitation of the aviation duties
4. The conditions of operation environments
Airman shall not perform any duty which was limited by the defect.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 43</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The items of failures which were granted for Waiver on Medical Exam shall nevertheless be required to be medical examined routinely. However, when CAA considers necessary or AME considers the condition of disease changes, such items shall be verified again for the Waiver on Medical Exam.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 44</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[CAA may at any time cancel the Waiver on Medical Exam previously granted, or may require the airman to suspend his performance of duties before any examination of assessments.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 45</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This Standard shall take effect on and from the date of promulgation.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
</法規>
